title: For Sale:  Classic Ruger Mark II +ammo/extras
postcontent: Original owner selling this beautiful Ruger Mark II Standard, in 22LR.  Produced in 1984.  The gun is in outstanding condition, with hardly any wear on the finish and perfect mechanical function.  Dad bought this gun back in 1985 when I was a kid--it was the first semi-auto pistol I fired.  I got older and moved on to other guns, and this Ruger went in dad's safe, where it sat for for 30 years.  He passed away a few years ago and I'm in the process of selling some of the guns from his collection.  I took this out to the range a few months ago and fired 50 rounds of 22LR through it without a hiccup--just as good as I remember from all those years ago.  After that I took it completely apart, inspected everything, and deep-cleaned it.  Now it's time to say goodbye and sell it as dad directed in his will (all his guns are to be sold for his only grandchild's college fund).Also included is 1000 rounds of assorted 22LR ammo (more than what's shown in the picture), everything from subsonic to hyper-velocity and Varmit HE.  The gun also comes with a hard plastic case and a nylon belt holster (never used).I will sell locally in Kitsap County or the Tacoma/JBLM area.  Cash or USPS Money Orders are the only forms of payment accepted.  Gun is sold as-is, with no warranty, and the sale is final.  Buyer is responsible for all fees associated with transfer, we can meet at the FFL of your choice to handle the transfer IAW WA law.
